cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.MA 

This paper deals with a machine learning problem involving exploration-exploitation tradeoff and regularization techniques, which are common topics in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The problem also involves matrix factorization and low-rank structure, which are relevant to the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the proposed algorithm involves optimization techniques, which are relevant to the sub-field of mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
